- The `Socket` will have the same file descriptor before and after the connection is made, because `Socket::connect` duplicates the file descriptor when creating the `Connection`.
- The `Connection` object will have a different file descriptor from the original `Socket` that it connected to the server. When the `Connection` object goes out of scope, it will correctly close its own file descriptor without affecting the `Socket` object's file descriptor.

